			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">I'm splitting this out from issue 2633.  We want to make the debug stub work on x86-32 Windows.  It already works on x86-64 Windows.

This will involve using the out-of-process debug exception handler to bounce untrusted faults back to the sel_ldr process for handling by the debug stub.  We will want to do this on both x86-32 and x86-64 Windows.  This will replace use of AddVectoredExceptionHandler() in win/thread_impl.cc.  It will allow the debug stub to handle out-of-stack conditions on Windows, and it will remove a security hole in the debug stub.
